HEADWORD: major axis
<hw>major axis</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <def>The greater
axis of a geometrical figure.</def> <specif>Especially</specif>:
<def>the longest axis of an ellipse or ellipsoid, which passes through
the two foci. See <er>Focus</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

